Chino Mayrina is currently a second year student majoring in English, Spanish and possibly French. More than just a whiz at languages, Chino is also a brilliant poet, often expressing his innermost emotions and private thoughts through the power of verse. When hes not writing, Chino is tutoring undergrads in Spanish, walking his bike on the sidewalk because his friends dont ride bikes, or cutting through the quad  the hypotenuse. Chino is also one of the founding editors of Nameless Magazine, a studentcreated, studentoriented, and studentrun quarterly online literary publication dedicated toward releasing the unheard voices of UC Daviss writers, artists and poets.
